<TITLE> Govt's power, gas price hike plan protested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 17 (bdnews24.com)The Communist Party of Bangladesh and Biplobi Workers' Party have protested the proposal to increase price of gas and electricity. CPB president Manjurul Ahsan Khan and general secretary Mujahidul Islam Selim in a statement on Friday said higher prices would make essential goods pricier and spell more sufferings for low-income people. They suggested the government rather curb corruption and wastage in the energy sector. President of the Biplobi Workers' Party Khandaker Ali Abbas and general secretary Saiful Huq in a separate statement asked the government not to tax people to raise funds to develop energy and power sector. They asked the government to postpone the initiative. Recently, the Power Development Board proposed for a 24 percent hike in the price of electricity. bd
